<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-12-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-01-01T20:00:00-05:00" n="1038" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d1038">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi></head>
                            <p>Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_AGV1">George V. Allen</persName> on
                                May 29, 1953 and Anil K. Chanda, Deputy Minister for External
                                Affairs, on June 24, 1953 signed and thereby brought into force an
                                agreement establishing a United States educational foundation in
                                India. For the text, see <gloss target="#t_TIAS1">TIAS</gloss> No.
                                2881, printed in 4 <gloss target="#t_UST1">UST</gloss> (pt. 2)
                                2288.</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>